--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- APPENDIX C  ::  ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Aquafield is organized into four layers:
--
--   1. PRIMITIVES   (Util.*)         -- New(), Tween(), Spring(), Ripple()...
--   2. EFFECTS      (Effects.*)      -- background particles, aurora, holo,
--                                       matrix rain, fireworks, shockwave
--   3. COMPONENTS   (tab:Create*)    -- Button, Toggle, Slider, Dropdown,
--                                       Input, Keybind, ColorPicker, Section
--   4. APPLICATION  (Aquafield.*)    -- Notify, Confirm, Tooltip, Palette,
--                                       Achievements, Configuration
--
-- Layers above MAY consume layers below; layers below MUST NOT depend on
-- anything above them.  This keeps the renderer testable and the effects
-- engine swappable.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- APPENDIX D  ::  PERFORMANCE NOTES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- * RunService.Heartbeat connections check `if not parent.Parent then ...
--   conn:Disconnect()` so dead UIs don't accumulate.
-- * The particle field defaults to 28 particles -- raise carefully; cost is
--   ~O(N) per frame and Roblox UI rendering is the bottleneck, not Lua.
-- * Use Aquafield.EffectsEnabled = false to disable ALL animated overlays at
--   once on low-spec machines.
-- * Tween creation is unpooled; for hot paths (e.g. drag), prefer assigning
--   property values directly instead of `Util.Tween(obj, 0, {...})`.
-- * The MatrixRain effect uses one TextLabel per column; 22 columns is the
--   comfortable cap on most machines.
