-- APPENDIX F  ::  FAQ
-- ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--
-- Q: Why exactly 5 themes?
-- A: Per project requirements. Aquafield:RegisterTheme is intentionally a no-op so theme count stays predictable across forks.
--
-- Q: My close/minimize icons were blank in v2.
-- A: Fixed in v3. We now render vector glyphs out of Frames + UICorner + UIStroke so no asset ID lookup is required.
--
-- Q: How do I disable all the fancy effects?
-- A: Set Aquafield.EffectsEnabled = false before creating the window, or toggle it from the auto-injected Settings tab.
--
-- Q: Can I add my own component?
-- A: Yes -- define a factory under Aquafield.ExtraComponents and call it with a tab.Page as the parent.
--
-- Q: Does configuration save on exit?
-- A: A debounced autosave runs every ~2s via Heartbeat. You can also call Aquafield:SaveConfiguration() manually.
--
-- Q: How do I trigger a fireworks burst manually?
-- A: Aquafield.Effects.Fireworks(parent, x, y, color). Position is in pixels relative to parent.
--
-- Q: Can I bind a hotkey other than K to toggle the UI?
-- A: Yes -- pass ToggleUIKeybind="J" (or any KeyCode name) to CreateWindow, or change it from Settings.
--
-- Q: Will it work in Studio?
-- A: Yes. CoreGui will fail to parent so it falls back to PlayerGui automatically.
--
-- Q: How big is the API surface?
-- A: ~50 public methods. The full set is enumerated in Appendix E (compatibility matrix).
--
-- Q: Is the source MIT?
-- A: Yes. See the license stub near the changelog block.
--
-- Q: Why are tabs flat-named in src/routes?
-- A: That is a different project. Aquafield is a Lua/Roblox UI library; tabs here are sidebar buttons that swap a ScrollingFrame in the content area.
--
-- Q: Can I have multiple windows?
-- A: Yes. Each CreateWindow call appends to Aquafield.Windows; each gets its own ScreenGui and toggle key listener.
